sec.p:
The process of the thermal analysis and life prediction of the exhaust manifold is as follows (Figure 4):


Construction of the finite element model for the hot end exhaust system with a part of cylinder head;

Temperature distribution during the thermal shock loading is determined based on the input data from gas flow simulation;

Three-dimensional temperature data are used to simulate the thermal stress analysis, which considers elasto-plastic material with temperature-dependent properties;

Prediction of the thermal fatigue life using CDM model.

Figure 4.
Analysis procedure of the exhaust manifold.
